SECTION 3.07. . If any amount of principal is not paid when due (whether at stated maturity, by acceleration or otherwise), that amount of principal shall bear interest, from the date on which such amount is due until such amount is paid in full, payable on demand, at a rate per annum equal at all times to two percent (2%) per annum above the interest rate in effect from time to time with respect to the applicable Loan, and with respect to any other overdue amount, the interest rate applicable to ABR Loans plus two percent (2%) per annum.
